    "In this section, when the attack mechanism takes effect, we will change the parameter p in Sect. 2.2.2.",
    "This parameter is used to control the switching between two attack behaviors and is an important parameter that affects the overall accuracy and stability of the algorithm.",
    "Set the parameter p to 0.3, 0.5, and 0.7 for experiments and compare it with the original parameter p = 0.9 to show the impact of parameter changes on BKA performance in the mechanism.",
